ithms with Python</a> course on Codecademy. </p>
<h2 id=3D"heading-frequently-asked-questions" class=3D"g-md-h2 gamut-tbxd0s=
-StyledText e8i0p5k0">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<h3 id=3D"heading-1-why-do-we-use-the-bfs-algorithm" class=3D"g-md-h3 gamut=
-t98mq7-StyledText e8i0p5k0">1. Why do we use the BFS algorithm?</h3>
<p class=3D"g-md-p">We use breadth-first search (BFS) to explore nodes in t=
he shortest possible way, making it ideal for identifying the shortest path=
 in unweighted graphs. </p>
<h3 id=3D"heading-2-is-bfs-used-in-ai" class=3D"g-md-h3 gamut-t98mq7-Styled=
Text e8i0p5k0">2. Is BFS used in AI?</h3>
<p class=3D"g-md-p">Yes. In artificial intelligence (AI), breadth-first sea=
rch is used in search strategies to explore all possible states or actions =
systematically. </p>
<h3 id=3D"heading-3-does-bfs-use-stack-or-queue" class=3D"g-md-h3 gamut-t98=
mq7-StyledText e8i0p5k0">3. Does BFS use stack or queue?</h3>
<p class=3D"g-md-p">The breadth-first search algorithm uses a queue to keep=
 track of nodes to be explored, ensuring that nodes are visited level by le=
vel in the order they were discovered. </p>
<h3 id=3D"heading-4-when-should-you-use-breadth-first-search" class=3D"g-md=
-h3 gamut-t98mq7-StyledText e8i0p5k0">4. When should you use breadth-first =
search?</h3>
<p class=3D"g-md-p">We should use breadth-first search when we need to find=
 the shortest path, explore all neighbors equally, or ensure complete trave=
rsal in level order. </p>
<h3 id=3D"heading-5-whats-the-difference-between-breadth-first-search-and-d=
ijkstras-algorithm" class=3D"g-md-h3 gamut-t98mq7-StyledText e8i0p5k0">5. W=
hat=E2=80=99s the difference between breadth-first search and Dijkstra=E2=
=80=99s algorithm?</h3>
<p class=3D"g-md-p">While breadth-first search works on unweighted graphs, =
Dijkstra=E2=80=99s algorithm is used for weighted graphs where edge costs v=
ary. BFS can be seen as a simplified version of Dijkstra=E2=80=99s algorith=
m with equal weights.</p>
